The voter registration drive started with a low turnout yesterday in most parts of Kilifi county.In most registration centres, people arrived in small numbers and some clerks said they had registered only 10 people by noon. There were no hitches recorded by the time we went to press.At Uwanjani polling centre, Sokoni ward, a handful of people lined up to register or confirm their voter registration details. &ldquo;Everything is going on well, although the attendance is low. Since we opened this station, we have only received 15 people. Some had come to confirm their voting cards. We are expecting that as we proceed, more people will come,&rdquo; clerk Ibrahim Yusuf said.Kilifi North IEBC coordinator Francis Runya said the drive started without a hitch. He said all the kits were delivered to the polling stations.